1. Purpose

Calculate norms within subregions (Subspaces) of hypersurfaces.
This takes general scalars, vectors, and tensors, and computes the
norms over coordinate spheres, weighting appropriately.

Sample use: quantifying violations of an assumed stress energy tensor
form over the inner region of the grid yet outside the BH, ignoring
refinement boundary points which are noisier.
